@Warren Woo I completely agree with your take on the graph. It's wild to see how much our priorities can change from application to graduation.
You nailed it with the point about high schoolers wanting to stay close to home. It's totally normal to feel nervous about leaving your comfort zone, but college really pushes you to grow in ways you don't expect. The small class size thing is so real too - once you've experienced those huge lecture halls, you start to crave those small class discussions.
I'm also curious about how this data might look internationally. There's gotta be some fascinating cultural differences there.

@Greta AOSE Thank you for these great comments. I think a particularly interesting wondering that you shared was: "Possibly if when adults were younger did they feel the same way high schoolers feel right now?"

Another way to phrase this: Did the opinions of the older group change as they aged? Or did the older group already go into college with different opinions than today's younger group?

What new analysis could we do to explore the questions above?
